Water and Sanitation Deputy Minister David Mahlobo. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - Water and Sanitation deputy minister David Mahlobo has tested positive for COVID-19.
He received his results on Thursday. The Presidency says Mahlobo is in good spirits and self-quarantining at home. READ: COVID-19: Zikalala concerned about frontline workers Those who have come into contact with him are self-isolating. The Presidency has wished Mahlobo and all South Africans who are battling the virus a speedy recovery. It has also sent condolences to those who lost their loved ones.